      "message": "\u003e Building Flutter appears to be very dependent on this structure, I tried many different ways of trying to change the directory name but ran into errors because this structure is hardcoded in their tools. \u0027src/flutter\u0027 is documented in their docs: https://github.com/brianosman/engine/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md and in the doc Kevin wrote: https://docs.google.com/document/d/19VuU-NPRvnj7eavH9Pwb8wfljpKBe-XWkVzuvnfDRtE/edit#heading\u003dh.hpzbjgghz5rt\n\u003e \n\u003e The problem is that Chromium also uses src in our recipes. Chromium is only built for CommandBuffer (Mac) builds and RecreateSKPs (GCE). I tested on a bot by building Flutter first and then building RecreateSKPs and it seemed to work.\n\u003e One way to make sure nothing unexpected happens would be to throw an exception if both need_flutter_checkout and need_chromium_checkout are true.\n\nNope, I was wrong: https://chromium-swarm.appspot.com/task?id\u003d34611eb200adba10\u0026refresh\u003d10\nMaking Flutter use src does cause the RecreateSKPs bot to fail when it tries to use src for Chromium. I wonder if the simple solution is to make Chromium use main_name\u003d\u0027chromium\u0027 for now and file a bug with flutter team asking them to call their top level src something else.",
